FOOT AND MOUTH DISEASE - KAZAKHSTAN (05): (EAST KAZAKHSTAN) BOVINE
******************************************************************

A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: 26 Aug 2011
Source: Kazakhstan Today [machine-translated, edited]
http://www.kt.kz/./?lang=rus&uin=1138536468&chapter=1153543712


An outbreak of foot and mouth disease recorded in East Kazakhstan
-----------------------------------------------------------------
In the East Kazakhstan village Karashilik, an outbreak of foot and
mouth disease [FMD] has been recorded, reports Kazakhstan Today.

"The entire affected village in East Kazakhstan has been quarantined.
The number of destroyed animals is counted in hundreds," said the
channel "CTC."

According to local residents, the village has burned 600 heads of
cattle and small ruminants. Allegedly, no one had paid attention to
FMD cases in a farm near the village, leading to a situation which is
deteriorating day by day.

Meanwhile, employees of a local akimat (a municipal district) argue
that the loss of cattle in the village stopped since several days.

On top of animal movement restrictions and other quarantine measures,
emergency vaccination, to protect the remaining healthy animals, has
been undertaken.

"Until now, infection is affecting cattle in spite of the steps. There
are farms in which all cattle are infected," said Asset Nurdybaev, a
villager from Karashilik.

--
